SIMPLE: insnare
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Insnare
<hw>In*snare"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Insnared</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Insnaring</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Written also
<ets>ensnare</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To catch in a snare; to entrap; to take by
artificial means.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Insnare</xex> a gudgeon.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Fenton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To take by wiles, stratagem, or deceit; to involve
in difficulties or perplexities; to seduce by artifice; to inveigle; to
allure; to entangle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>insnaring</qex> charms⟦br⟧
Of love's soft queen.</q> <rj><qau>Glover.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insnarer</ent>⟦br⟧
